\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\fs28\ul\cf1\insrsid10909999\charrsid10909999 Keep a small list.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cf1\insrsid10909999\charrsid10909999 
\par When I was younger, I had huge lists of people \endash  just about everybody I knew, subdivided into all kinds of categories. It was too big for me, and I fell into the trap of not prayin
g for anybody at all on some days when the idea of reading that huge list fatigued me before I started. Remember: }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\cf1\insrsid10909999\charrsid10909999 \'93It is better to do a little thing than fail to do a large thing
\'94}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cf1\insrsid10909999\charrsid10909999 . 
\par 
\par Either keep a small list, with family, friends, your pastor, and your ene
mies or those who have offended you or disturb your soul in some way. It should not be book size. Some will make a list for Monday and another for Tuesday, etc. If you are that organized, I salute and admire you. The important thing is to have a manageabl
e list of people for each day. 
\par 
\par I like lists, because even though I know all my parishioner\rquote s names by heart, it gets very fatiguing to call to mind all their names. I use my diptychs}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cf1\super\insrsid10909999\charrsid10909999 \chftn 
{\footnote\ftnalt \ltrpar \pard\plain \ltrpar\s25\ql \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid10909999 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs20\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs20\lang1033\langfe255\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af35\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp255 {
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\super\insrsid5513235 \chftn }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5513235 \hich\af0\dbch\af35\loch\f0 \hich\f0  \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Diptych\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0 
 means list. All priests have one, and they use it to commemorate the living and the dead in the \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Proskimidie\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  or \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Preparation service\'94\loch\f0  bef\hich\af0\dbch\af35\loch\f0 
ore the Divine Liturgy, by taking out a small piece and putting it on the diskos (the round plate on a small stand that is used with the chalice) for each name. This bread is latter added to the chalice after the faithful are communed, with the prayer }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f169\insrsid5513235\charrsid12264569 \loch\af169\dbch\af35\hich\f169 \'93\loch\f169 By \hich\af169\dbch\af35\loch\f169 \hich\f169 
thy precious Blood, O Lord, wash away the sins of those here commemorated, through the intercessions of Thy saints\'94}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5513235 \hich\af0\dbch\af35\loch\f0 
 Only the Orthodox are commemorated in this way (since only the Orthodox may have Holy Communion), but most priests are like me and have many\hich\af0\dbch\af35\loch\f0 
 non Orthodox in their diptychs that they pray for without taking out particles of bread. 
\par }}}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cf1\insrsid10909999\charrsid10909999  for this purpose. 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\fs28\ul\cf1\insrsid10909999\charrsid10909999 Have a set time. 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cf1\insrsid10909999\charrsid10909999 
\par If you have a set time to pray for others, you will pray for others. Some suggested times: after morning (better) or evening prayers and during your commute in the car, bus or train (but don\rquote 
t forget the off days!)  When I was in an office I would go outside and walk on some railroad tracks and pray for people. It was a great break from work
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\fs28\ul\cf1\insrsid10909999\charrsid10909999 Pray for your enemies. 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cf1\insrsid10909999\charrsid10909999 
\par This seems obvious, since our Lord commanded us: 
\par 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \li576\ri576\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\rin576\lin576\itap0\pararsid10909999 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f169\cf1\insrsid10909999\charrsid10909999 \'93\'85
 Love your enemies, bless them that curse you, do good to them that hate you, and pray for them which despitefully use you, and persecute you\rquote  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f169\fs16\cf1\insrsid10909999\charrsid10909999 (Matthew 5:44) }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f169\cf1\insrsid10909999\charrsid10909999 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid10909999 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cf1\insrsid10909999\charrsid10909999 
\par In my experience as a pastor, this idea does not always occur to us, or we are resistant to it.  
\par 
\par It is }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\cf1\insrsid10909999\charrsid10909999 IMPERATIVE}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cf1\insrsid10909999\charrsid10909999 
 that you pray for your enemies, or those of whom you have any bitterness, towards, remember wrongs, e
tc. You know the people of whom your soul feels darker and colder and angry when you think of them or encounter them. Listen to your soul! Sometimes this coldness is disguised from us, but if you are attentive to yourself, you will feel when your peace is
 disturbed by the thought of or interaction with someone. This is always your fault! There is no keeping score here \endash  it does not matter if \'93he/she/they\'94 were at fault too. You should not dare to disobey a direct commandment of the Lord. 

\par 
\par We cannot love as God loves without learning to forgive our enemies. Don\rquote 
t think of an enemy as only someone that you might come to blows with or are in some kind of open conflict with. Learn to feel the chilling darkness from that dark shadow that blocks out the warmth of the sun from your soul. 
\par 
\par It is more important to pray for your enemies, those who curse you, and hate you than yourself or your loved ones. God hears our prayer when it is pure. Bad feelings about others make us impure. It is as simple as that, and besid
es, the Lord commanded us. 
\par 
\par Just do it; make a list of people you have problems with. Don\rquote t write a novel \endash  there is no need to include biographical information! 
\par 
\par Pray for these people everyday, simply, resolutely, and even if your prayer is accompanied with anger and clenched teeth. 
\par 
\par It is MUCH better to pray and fight against anger than to be angry and not pray. You need to fight off the anger, and the only way is to forgive, and the best way to forgive is to pray. 
\par 
\par Do not let yourself be fooled \endash  the snake in the grass that we see is less dangerous than the one we do not see. Just because we do not feel anger when we do }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\cf1\insrsid10909999\charrsid10909999 not}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cf1\insrsid10909999\charrsid10909999  think of someone does not prove anything! Just try thinking of those certain people in your life, and see if you feel any darkness. And then try praying for them \endash 
 any anger or any kind of darkening of the soul during this time is a sure sign that you must pray for them \endash  for your sake as well as theirs. 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\fs28\ul\cf1\insrsid10909999\charrsid10909999 How to pray for others.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\ul\cf1\insrsid10909999\charrsid10909999  
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cf1\insrsid10909999\charrsid10909999 
\par God knows the needs of all of us. In general, it is best to pray simply.  You could say }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f169\cf1\insrsid10909999\charrsid10909999 \'93Lord have mercy on }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f169\cf6\insrsid10909999\charrsid10909999 (name)}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f169\cf1\insrsid10909999\charrsid10909999 \'94 }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cf1\insrsid10909999\charrsid10909999 for each person, or use the Jesus prayer: 
\par 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \li576\ri576\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\rin576\lin576\itap0\pararsid10909999 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f169\cf1\insrsid10909999\charrsid10909999 \'93Lord Jesus Christ, Son of God, have mercy on }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\b\f169\cf6\insrsid10909999\charrsid10909999 (name)}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f169\cf1\insrsid10909999\charrsid10909999 .\'94
\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid10909999 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f169\cf1\insrsid10909999\charrsid10909999 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid10909999 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cf1\insrsid10909999\charrsid10909999 Some may want to mention particular needs, but it is best to keep it simple. The intercesso
ry prayers of the church are a good guide. The more specific you get, the more you think, and the less you pray, and there is always a danger that you will sin by judging others. 
\par 
